Text	The bombings of Air India Flight 182 and the Narita Airport launched several investigations , inquiries and trials .	The trial of Malik and Bagri is known as the Air India Trial ; events relating to the incident are listed below in chronological order .	- July 1985 Canadian Prime Minister Brian Mulroney calls Indian Prime Minister Rajiv Gandhi to offer his condolences , but does not call the victims ' families to do the same .	This causes an uproar among Indo - Canadians who feel that although this is the deadliest terrorist act to date , it is not taken seriously because the victims although mostly Canadian were not Caucasian .	- 8 November 1985 The RCMP charge Talwinder Singh Parmar and Inderjit Singh Reyat with weapons , explosives and conspiracy offenses after a raid on their homes .
